        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:16PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 22 miles northeast of
Sanderson to 10 miles south of Terrell County Gas Plant to 11 miles
north of Langtry. Movement was southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sanderson, Dryden, Terrell County Gas Plant, and Terrell County
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
